<text xml:lang="ta" type="edition">
  <body>
    <div rend="parallel">
      <lg xml:id="TolE0340">
<l>tēṉeṉ kiḷavi valleḻut tiyaiyiṉ</l>
<l>mēṉilai yottalum valleḻuttu mikutalu</l>
<l>māmuṟai yiraṇṭu murimaiyu muṭaittē</l>
<l>valleḻuttu mikuvaḻi yiṟuti yillai</l>
      </lg>
      <lg xml:lang="en">
<l>When the word <foreign xml:lang="ta">tēṉ</foreign> ' honey ' is followed by a plosive,</l>
<l>it will either have the above-described change or the doubling</l>
<l>of the plosive ; the two rules are both appropriate ;</l>
<l>when the plosive doubles, there is no final [<foreign xml:lang="ta">ṉ</foreign>].<note place="foot">i.e. <foreign xml:lang="ta">tēṉ + kuṭam &gt; tēṉkuṭam / tēṟkuṭam | tēkkuṭam.</foreign></note></l>
      </lg>
    </div>
  </body>
